A pressure group within ruling All Progressives Congress, APC Coalition Network International (APCN), has announced the appointment of Hon. Oluwarotimi Olatunbosun Balogun as the new chairman of the Lagos state chapter of the group. In a statement signed by the National President of the APCN, Prof. Muhammad Omolaja, he said the new Lagos chairman need no introduction given competence, political and professional relevance. Balogun who was one of the aspirants who contested Ikorodu Constituency seat with the Lagos Assembly Majority Leader, Hon. Sania. O. Agunbiade, during the 2019 elections. Omolaja urged members of APCN both at home and abroad to give absolute support to the new chairman while wishing him a successful tenure in office.